• Start date flexible, but ideally someone who can ramp up quickly.

• Experienced Penetration Tester with 4+ years in IAM and Identity Risk Management; 
• Proficient in Burp Suite, Nmap, and Windows exploitation techniques;
• Strong understanding of Microsoft Azure AD and AWS Cognito; 
• Experience with cloud-based security tools such as Okta and OneLogin;
• Solid programming skills in Python, Java, or C++;
• 3+ years of experience working with Fortune 500 companies;
• US citizenship with Secret clearance (active);
• Able to start on November 7th or sooner;
• Willing to relocate to Minneapolis area for full-time opportunity;
• Must be authorized to work in the United States without sponsorship.

• Senior Full-Time Penetration Tester with 5+ years of experience in Ethical Hacking and Red Teaming required; 
• Must have strong understanding of Identity and Access Management (IAM) concepts and hands-on experience with cloud-based IAM systems; 
• Familiarity with Security Incident Response Teams (SIRT) processes and participation in SOC (Security Operations Center) activities is a must; 
• Proficiency in Python, Burp Suite, Nmap, and Aircrack-ng required, along with knowledge of Linux/Unix operating systems; 
• Strong written and verbal communication skills for effective collaboration with development teams; 
• Must be able to obtain US Department of State-issued Clearance Level 2 clearance for international travel; 
• Availability to start in 60 days with a flexible schedule (remote/onsite);

• Experienced frontend developer with 3+ years in React and Next.js, hands-on expertise with Tailwind CSS, strong understanding of SCSS; seniority: mid-level to senior;
• Must have experience with state management (e.g., Redux) and caching (e.g., Redis); familiarity with popular frontend build tools like Webpack, Babel, and ESLint a plus;
• Strong front-end development skills for crafting high-quality UI/UX, proficiency in creating reusable reusable components and styling with CSS-in-JS (e.g., Styled Components);
• Must be proficient in modern JavaScript syntax including async/await, classes, and destructuring; experience with ES6+ features like class properties and optional chaining a plus;
• 2+ years’ experience working on scalable, maintainable frontend architectures; expertise in creating reusable components, managing state, and handling errors through proper logging and debugging tools;
• Strong written and verbal communication skills for collaborating with cross-functional teams (DevOps, Design, Product) to deliver high-quality products within tight timelines; ability to work independently and prioritize tasks effectively.
• Start date: ASAP, flexible start date a plus.

